Overview

I designed and developed a visual identity and internal marketing campaign for a workplace literature club. The goal was to increase engagement, build awareness, and create a recognisable identity for the initiative across internal communication channels.

Objective

The primary objective of this project was to transform a newly created workplace club into a visually engaging and recognisable internal brand. The focus was on:

Increasing awareness of the literature club

Encouraging participation from colleagues

Creating a consistent and appealing visual identity

Delivering content suitable for internal digital communication channels


My Role

Visual identity design (logo creation)

Concept development for internal marketing campaign

Motion/animated content design for internal announcements

Visual consistency across campaign materials


Process

1. Brand Concept Development

I began by defining the tone and personality of the literature club. The aim was to strike a balance between creativity, accessibility, and a sense of community. This guided the visual direction and messaging style.

2. Logo Design

I created a logo that reflects the essence of reading, ideas, and shared discussion. The design focuses on clarity and recognisability, ensuring it works across different internal platforms and formats.

3. Campaign Visual Direction

I developed a consistent visual style to be used across all promotional materials. This included:

Typography choices aligned with a readable and modern aesthetic

A cohesive colour palette suitable for workplace environments

Simple, engaging visual hierarchy for quick readability


4. Animated Content Creation

To increase visibility and engagement, I designed animated content intended for internal company channels. These animations were created to:

Capture attention quickly in busy digital environments

Communicate the purpose of the club in a clear and engaging way

Encourage participation through visual storytelling

Tools used: Canva and Figma 


Outcome

The final output was a cohesive internal campaign that introduced and promoted the literature club in a visually engaging way. The materials were designed for easy sharing across internal communication channels and aimed at increasing awareness and participation.

Tools & Skills Used

Visual identity design

Branding and communication strategy

Motion/animation design

Layout and composition

Audience-focused content creation


Reflection

This project allowed me to combine creativity with practical communication design in a real workplace setting. It strengthened my ability to design for an audience, maintain visual consistency, and think strategically about engagement within an organisation.
